modules.description: Provides functions to check for the presence of media in a CDROM device and retrieve its status. Works with system-specific identifiers and device paths. Used to determine if a CDROM drive contains a disc before attempting to read from it.

Converts CD-ROM drive and disc status values to human-readable strings, queries the current status of a CD-ROM drive and its contents, and retrieves the MCN (Universal Product Code) from a CD-ROM device. Operates on custom status types representing drive and disc conditions. Used to monitor CD-ROM hardware state and identify inserted media.
